{"name": "itanium-demangler", "metadata": {"name": "itanium-demangler", "version": "1.1", "classifiers": ["Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/whitequark/python-itanium_demangler", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Pure Python parser for mangled itanium symbols", "upload_time": 1661005974}, "documentation": ["# Itanium Demangler\n\nThe *Python Itanium Demangler* is a pure Python parser for the [Itanium C++ ABI symbol mangling language][manglang]. Note that MSVC mangling language is not supported.\n\nThis demangler generates an abstract syntax tree from mangled symbols, which can be used for directly extracting type information, as opposed to having to interpret the C++ source code corresponding to the demangled symbol\n\n There is also a built-in AST stringifier, so the demangler can be used as a replacement for `c++filt` or for formatting backtraces.\n\n[manglang]: https://itanium-cxx-abi.github.io/cxx-abi/abi.html#mangling\n\n## Requirements\n\nThe demangler runs on Python 2.7 and 3.3+ and has no dependencies.\n\n## Installation\n\nInstalling via PyPI:\n\n    pip install itanium_demangler\n\nUsing a local repository for development:\n\n    git clone https://github.com/whitequark/python-itanium_demangler\n    cd python-itanium_demangler\n    python setup.py develop --user\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom itanium_demangler import parse as demangle\n\nast = demangle(\"_ZN5boost6chrono24process_system_cpu_clock3nowEv\")\n\nprint(repr(ast))\n# <FuncNode func <Node qual_name (<Node name 'boost'>, <Node name 'chrono'>, <Node name 'process_system_cpu_clock'>, <Node name 'now'>)> (<Node builtin 'void'>,) None>\n\nprint(ast)\n# boost::chrono::process_system_cpu_clock::now()\n```\n\n## Future considerations\n\nA similar (i.e. also parsing to an AST) implementation of a demangler for the MSVC mangling language would be useful to have.\n\n## License\n\n[0-clause BSD](LICENSE-0BSD.txt)\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "itanium_demangler", "documentation": ["encoding:utf-8"], "functions": [{"name": "itanium_demangler._handle_cv", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "qualifiers", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "node", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._handle_indirect", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "qualifier", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "node", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_number", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_seq_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_until_end", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "kind", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fn", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_source_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "is_nested", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_type", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_expr_primary", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._expand_template_args", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_encoding", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_special", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._parse_mangled_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cursor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._expand_arg_packs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ast", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler.parse", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "raw", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler.is_ctor_or_dtor", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ast", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "itanium_demangler.name", "type": null, "documentation": ["This module implements a C++ Itanium ABI demangler.\n\nThe demangler provides a single entry point, `demangle`, and returns either `None`\nor an abstract syntax tree. All nodes have, at least, a `kind` field.\n\nName nodes:\n    * `name`: `node.value` (`str`) holds an unqualified name\n    * `ctor`: `node.value` is one of `\"complete\"`, `\"base\"`, or `\"allocating\"`, specifying\n      the type of constructor\n    * `dtor`: `node.value` is one of `\"deleting\"`, `\"complete\"`, or `\"base\"`, specifying\n      the type of destructor\n    * `oper`: `node.value` (`str`) holds a symbolic operator name, without the keyword\n      \"operator\"\n    * `oper_cast`: `node.value` holds a type node\n    * `tpl_args`: `node.value` (`tuple`) holds a sequence of type nodes\n    * `qual_name`: `node.value` (`tuple`) holds a sequence of `name` and `tpl_args` nodes,\n      possibly ending in a `ctor`, `dtor` or `operator` node\n    * `abi`: `node.value` holds a name node, `node.qual` (`frozenset`) holds a set of ABI tags\n\nType nodes:\n    * `name` and `qual_name` specify a type by its name\n    * `builtin`: `node.value` (`str`) specifies a builtin type by its name\n    * `pointer`, `lvalue` and `rvalue`: `node.value` holds a pointee type node\n    * `cv_qual`: `node.value` holds a type node, `node.qual` (`frozenset`) is any of\n      `\"const\"`, `\"volatile\"`, or `\"restrict\"`\n    * `literal`: `node.value` (`str`) holds the literal representation as-is,\n      `node.ty` holds a type node specifying the type of the literal\n    * `function`: `node.name` holds a name node specifying the function name,\n      `node.ret_ty` holds a type node specifying the return type of a template function,\n      if any, or `None`, ``node.arg_tys` (`tuple`) holds a sequence of type nodes\n      specifying thefunction arguments\n\nSpecial nodes:\n    * `vtable`, `vtt`, `typeinfo`, and `typeinfo_name`: `node.value` holds a type node\n      specifying the type described by this RTTI data structure\n    * `nonvirt_thunk`, `virt_thunk`: `node.value` holds a function node specifying\n      the function to which the thunk dispatches"]}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._ctor_dtor_map", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._std_names", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._operators", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._builtin_types", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._NUMBER_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._SOURCE_NAME_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "itanium_demangler._NAME_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {